at which of the four levels of love do you struggle to attain st bernard describes the levels of loving as loving others for your own sake loving god for what he can do for you loving god for god's sake loving yourself and others for god's sake i am moved by st bernard's clarity on how we progress through our lives as we learn how to be the loving creatures that god created maybe only the saints attain level i watch children grow and i see them clearly struggle with level most adults seem stuck somewhere between and people of faith who work at it seem to be able to spend some time at level you can especially see this in the saints as they describe how they love god as if they are describing a beautiful work of art or a lover i seem to be struggling to attain level i have trouble loving myself for me let alone god i love others for my own sake not yet for god's i still have much to learn god is patient with me Current teachings of Prem Rawat Justification (theology) Salvation Trinity Love Simone Weil Jewish views of religious pluralism Sola fide F. Scott Fitzgerald Opus Dei God John Howard Yoder Saint Paul of Tarsus Theosis Idolatry Roman Catholic Church Comparing and contrasting Judaism and Christianity Christian view of marriage Tulsidas Mary, the mother of Jesus Jiddu Krishnamurti Mortification of the flesh Merit Baptism Sheikh Abdullah Evil Summa Theologiae John the Baptist Religious Society of Friends Humphrey Bogart Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Original sin Mitnagdim Sin Storytelling Arjuna Confession Presuppositional apologetics Community of Christ Brave New World The Tale of Genji Ten Commandments Urantia Maimonides Darwin from Orchids to Variation Charles Grandison Finney A Course In Miracles Bah__'__ Faith and Science Bernard of Clairvaux Moral objectivism Miss Saigon Filioque clause Canonization Nicomachean Ethics Ascetical theology Origin belief Sikhism Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints Francis of Assisi C. S. Lewis Sabbath Vishnu sahasranama Sake D